m long CCT dipole layout consisting of two\ncoils. The superconductor is a commercially available 0.33 mm wire with\npolyimide insulation in a 6-around-1 cable. The channels in the coil formers,\nthat determine the CCT layout, allow for 2 x 5 cable layers. A total of 70\nwindings makes that the coil current can be kept below 100 A. We will present\nthe detailed design and preliminary quench simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Feb 2022 15:31:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-05"}
